    "summary": "I am currently Professor of International Management with the Global Economics & Management department at the University of Groningen. Previously I was  Academic Director of the Bachelor program in International Business and, before that, associate professor and director of the MBA program at the University of Amsterdam Business School. From 2008 until 2011 I taught International Business at the University of Washington\u2019s Michael G. Foster School of Business. My research centers on the intrinsic- and extrinsic drivers of corporate social behaviors, particularly in a cross border setting. My work has been published in outlets such as Academy of Management Review, Strategic Management Journal, Journal of Management Studies, Journal of Business Ethics, and Business & Society. Beyond that I try to be an active member of the academic community, for instance serving as an Associate Editor for Business & Society, and on the Editorial Boards of Academy of Management Discoveries, Journal of International Business Policy and Business Ethics, the Environment, and Responsibility, in addition to ad hoc reviewing for a host of other journals. \n\nAreas of interest: internationalization and international strategy, CSR, corporate philanthropy",
